ike to work (even do work/life balance should be important). I don\'t need a lot of people in my life, maybe I don\'t need a lot of people in my life. But I wouldn\'t like a life with a lot of responsibilities (kids, mortgage, credit card debt). I would like a life with a lot of change. I would like to live in a lot of different places in the world. I don\'t want to grow old. I want to walk to work. I want to live in the city. I would like to live in a place where things are actually happening. I would like to go out to dinner from time to time. I would like to tap dance my way to work, not because i get paid to much, but because i spend the right amount of time working in something that is interesting and exciting. I want to have a life of learning. I like learning. I like doing different things. I get tired quite easily and quickly of things. I can adapt to change pretty quickly. I want to meet people and have friends. I don\'t need it, but i like to be around people more than i like maintaining relationships. I don\'t need to be rich, but I would like to cause a change in whatever i\'m doing, even if it\'s minimal. I want to be great at whatever I do. I want to have a simple and fulfilling life, without the pressures of society hanging on over me, being creative, trying out new things and live the life I want.','1-10-2011','','publish','open','open','','1-10-2011','','','2012-01-11 00:34:57','2012-01-11 00:34:57','',0,'http://vrasen.com/xyz/?p=40',0,'post','',0),(24,1,'2012-01-02 20:05:55','2012-01-02 20:05:55','the future. i wonder a lot about. we, as human individuals, are many times unable to see in the macro terms of history. how do i fit into these time lapses? should be thinking of it in this way, or just go about my day as the worker ant in the colony? the life of the colony is always a lot longer and more monumental than the life of the worker ant? is it human nature to ignore the macro time frame imposed by the the institution of time upon us? i don not 