elf to have. On the other, I feel as if my life is not going anywhere. It is at this moment that I start to think about my legacy, and what I want for myself. At the same time, what would make me happy? Should I even do things because of my happiness. What will make me happy in the future? I don\'t think I know. Happiness should never be a goal in my life, but what should I peruse then. What interests me more? In grad school, I have found a new relationship with the knowledge I had before coming here. I\'ve found out more interesting and more relevant, but at the same time I find my artistic inclinations go deeper. What should I do? I think the right path will come to me at the right time. In the meantime, I wish to have as many new experiences as possible and meet as many people as possible. These things always please me.\r\n\r\nMaybe, I should examine a bit deeper what I really want out of life. More than anything, I\'m just living, i\'m not committing suicide right now. I\'m not living for anything in particular. I don\'t think I have to live for anything. Should I? I don\'t know if I have any particular mission in life, except for my curiosity and willingness to learn and have new experiences. I should definitely think a little bit more about all this...','2-6-2012','','publish','open','open','','2-6-2012','','','2012-02-06 14:10:11','2012-02-06 14:10:11','',0,'http://vrasen.com/xyz/?p=60',0,'post','',0),(57,1,'2012-01-29 14:36:42','2012-01-29 14:36:42','I was thinking about what I want to do with my life. I am thinking about what should I do with my life and what would make me happier. What I am noticing is that it is all very location oriented. I wish to go places, visit the world, but maybe I don\'t really know for what. I should make a \"bucket list\", but I should start thinking about it in another way. I want to find out things I want to do that are location independent. Traveling is fine and dandy, but if all you want to do is travel then maybe you should